s demonstrates an extensive chromosomal reorganization within the two lineages of nectarivorous phyllostomids, with a large number of chromosomes shared between M. californicus and G. soricina. We show that the evolution of nectar-feeding bats occurs mainly by reshuffling of chiropteran Evolutionarily Conserved Units (ECUs). Robertsonian fusions/fissions and inversions seem to be important modifiers of phyllostomid karyotypes, and autapomorphic character states are common within species. Macrotus californicus chromosome paints will be a valuable tool for documenting the pattern of karyotypic evolution within Phyllostomidae radiation.", "access_right": "restricted", "creators": [{"name": "Sotero-Caio, Cibele G", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Volleth, Marianne", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Gollahon, Lauren S", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Fu, Beiyuan", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Cheng, William", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Ng, Bee L", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Yang, Fengtang", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Baker, Robert J", "affiliation": null}], "keywords": ["Biodiversity", "Mammalia", "Chiroptera", "Chordata", "Animalia", "bats", "bat"], "related_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/a9fd1e66a4e31ce6c9f4a92c82d5fd89", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://sha256/da5a0103adb2f470604393a1a910187680cb56b47680fabfe7d39a7ceab2ed84", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "zotero://select/groups/5435545/items/B3CBHRKU", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://zotero.org/groups/5435545/items/B3CBHRKU", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://linker.bio/cut:hash://md5/14822be374e44ca58baa13a4d4630e59!/b263227-265706", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://md5/26f7ce5dd404e33c6570edd4ba250d20", "relation": "isPartOf", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "10.5281/zenodo.1410543", "relation": "isCompiledBy", "